article.description: Sam Hughes scored 17, and Ahmad Thomas had 15 points with 10 rebounds to help UNC Asheville beat Liberty 73-56 Thursday night.
article.headline: Hughes, Thomas lead UNC Asheville past Liberty, 73-56
article.linkText: Hughes, Thomas lead UNC Asheville past Liberty, 73-56
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. -- Sam Hughes scored 17, and Ahmad Thomas had 15 points with 10 rebounds to help UNC Asheville beat Liberty 73-56 Thursday night. Kevin Vannatta added 13 points for UNC Asheville, which secured a first-round bye in next week's Big South Conference tournament. A jumper by Vannatta capped a 10-2 run that put the Bulldogs (19-10, 12-5) up 19-7 with 12 minutes left in the first half. Two free throws by Evan Maxwell cut the Liberty (12-18, 9-8) deficit to three just more than five minutes later, but Asheville scored 16 of the final 19 points of the half to take 35-19 lead into the break. It was the Flames' third-lowest scoring half of the season. A.C. Reid led Liberty with 11 points. Lovell Cabbil scored 10. UNC Asheville held a 42-31 edge on the glass and limited the Flames to 37.7 percent (20-of-53) shooting.
